  <text>
    <!-- のみ・しらみ・うま・の・しと・する・まくら・もと   -->
    <l>
      <orig><ji k="のみ">蚤</ji><ji k="しらみ">虱</ji></orig>
      <trans lang="en">I arise early to lice</trans>
    </l>
    <l>
      <orig><ji k="うま">馬</ji>の<ji k="しと">尿</ji>する</orig>
      <trans lang="en">and fleas, when a horse pisses</trans>
    </l>
    <l>
      <orig><ji k="まくら">枕</ji>もと</orig>
      <trans lang="en">Next to my pillow</trans>
    </l>
  </text>
  <commentary>
    <remarks>
      <p>The original is more compressed than the translation: that the poet is awakened
        by the horse is only implicit.</p>
    </remarks>
    <theme>Summer</theme>
    <link href="http://carlsensei.com/classical/index.php/text/view/129"/>
    <link href="http://www.bentenkaku.jp/eng/highlights/hojin.html">Some background info on this famous poem.</link>
    <lookup>蝨</lookup>
    <lookup>马</lookup>
  </commentary>
